50|$|The Jaghalkani-i-Takhta Pul <b>massacres</b> {{took place}} near Mazari Sharif, Afghanistan in 1998, and {{involved}} hundreds of victims <b>massacred</b> by the Taliban.|$|R
50|$|The <b>Massacres</b> of Badr Khan were {{a series}} of <b>massacres</b> {{carried out by the}} Kurdish Emirs of Bohtan and Hakkari, Badr Khan and Nurallah, against the Assyrians of Hakkari and Tiyari in the 1840s. The <b>massacres</b> {{resulted}} in the killing of more than 10,000 Assyrians and the captivity of thousands of others.|$|R
